Data Products: Leaflet project

Jason Schmidt

August 13, 2017

Overview

The following map was created using leaflet. It depicts the distribution of property total taxable values in Orange County, California 2016.

mf<-read.csv("~/coursera/data scientist/Data products/mf.csv")

Creating the plot.

mfcolour<-colorQuantile("Reds",mf$taxablevaluetotal,n=4)

mprops<- leaflet(mf) %>%
        addTiles() %>%
        addCircles(weight=1, lng=mf$longitude,lat=mf$latitude, 
                   label =paste("Property value: " ,formatC(mf$taxablevaluetotal, 
                                                            format="d",big.mark=",")),
                   color = ~mfcolour(taxablevaluetotal), radius=mf$taxablevaluetotal/50000) %>%
        addLegend("bottomleft", pal = mfcolour, values = ~taxablevaluetotal,
                  title = "Property Value Percentile",
                  labFormat = labelFormat(prefix = "$"),opacity = 1
  )
        
mprops
